         <div type="transcription">
            <p><milestone unit="passage" n="4.1d-4.5d"/>
<lb corresp="#a1"/><gap reason="lost"/><gap reason="plain" quantity="1"/><w>sadā</w><w>smṛtā<supplied>ḥ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a2"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>kärso</supplied>rmeṃ</w><pc>•</pc><w>apramā<supplied>dasya</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>pramudye</supplied>ta</w><pc>•</pc><w>snai-ykorñe<supplied>cce</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#a4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>a</supplied>p<supplied>ra</supplied>m<supplied>a</supplied>t<supplied>tāḥ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b3"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>bhū</supplied>m<supplied>i</supplied>sth<supplied>ā</supplied>n</w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b4"/><gap reason="lost"/><w>aiśaumye</w><w>aknāts<supplied>aṃ</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b5"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>saṃyame</supplied>na</w><w>damena</w><w>c<supplied>a</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/>
<lb corresp="#b6"/><gap reason="lost"/><w><supplied>aiś</supplied>aumye</w><pc>•</pc><w>tam</w><w>ogh<supplied>o</supplied></w><gap reason="lost"/></p>
         </div>
         <div type="translation">
            <p><choice corresp="#a1"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (who are negligent are) always remembered</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a2"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] recognising (this characteristic) [SKT] as one of the diligent, (the wise) ...</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] ... should rejoice (in diligence) [TB] ... (should rejoice) in diligence</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#a4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] The diligent, (constant,)</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b3"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] (like one standing on a mountain) [observes] those standing on the ground [below]</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b4"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] the wise (looks down on) fools</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b5"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[SKT] with effort and with discipline</seg></seg></choice><choice corresp="#b6"><seg><seg type="prim_transl">[TB] the wise (makes an island) [SKT] that a flood does not destroy</seg></seg></choice></p>
         </div>
         <div type="comments">
            <p><note type="parallels"><bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>126-127</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:levi1912a"/><citedRange>235-241</citedRange></bibl>; <bibl><title corresp="ref:hahn2007"/><citedRange>23</citedRange></bibl></note><note type="remarks">The upper margin of the recto (lower of the verso) is preserved. Lines a1-4 cover the 6 half pādas 4.1d-4.3a, lines b3-6 the 6 half pādas 4.4e-4.5d: the 7 half pādas in between will have covered two lines on each side and the total number of lines must have been 6. On <ref target="http://idp.bl.uk/database/oo_loader.a4d?pm=IOL%20Toch%20928" type="external">IDP</ref>, recto and verso are reversed.</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment">Uv.4.1d <hi>ye pramattāḥ sadā mṛtāḥ</hi>, see Dhp.21 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#a1" type="philcomment"><hi>smṛtā(ḥ)</hi> seems to be an error for <hi>mṛtāḥ</hi>, possibly induced by <hi>sadā</hi> (also in the Tib. version, see <bibl><title corresp="ref:levi1912a"/><citedRange>235</citedRange></bibl>), which corresponds to <hi>yathā</hi> in e.g. the Dhp. Thus, Dhp.21d <hi>ye pamattā yathā matā</hi> 'the careless are as though [already] dead' (<bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>) corresponds to <hi>ye pramattāḥ sadā smṛtāḥ</hi> 'who are negligent are always remembered' in this version (this reading is not given by <bibl><title corresp="ref:bernhard1965"/><citedRange>126</citedRange></bibl>).</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">Uv.4.2a-b <hi>etāṃ viśeṣatāṃ jñātvā hy apramādasya paṇḍitaḥ</hi>, see Dhp.22 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#a2" type="philcomment">The hiatus-resolving <hi>hy</hi> is lacking before <hi>apramā(dasya)</hi> (this occurs frequently with these pādas divided in two, because there is no hiatus anyway, cf. <bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1974"/><citedRange>82</citedRange></bibl>, <bibl><title corresp="ref:thomas1977a"/><citedRange>271</citedRange></bibl> and e.g. <ref type="ms" target="txt:m-tht101"/> a3 <hi>as(m)iṃ</hi> for <hi>hy asmiṃ</hi>).</note><note corresp="#a3" type="philcomment">Uv.4.2c <hi>apramādaṃ pramudyeta</hi>, see Dhp.22 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#a4" type="philcomment">Uv.4.3a <hi>apramattāḥ sātatikā</hi>, see Dhp.23(and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b3" type="philcomment">Uv.4.4e <hi>parvatasthaiva bhūmisthāṃ</hi>, see Dhp.28 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b4" type="philcomment">Uv.4.4f <hi>dhīro bālān avekṣate</hi>, see Dhp.28 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b5" type="philcomment">Uv.4.5b <hi>saṃyamena damena ca</hi>, see Dhp.25 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note><note corresp="#b6" type="philcomment">Uv.4.5c-d <hi>dvīpaṃ karoti medhāvī tam ogho nābhimardati</hi>, see Dhp.25 (and <bibl><title corresp="ref:norman2004"/><citedRange>4</citedRange></bibl>)</note></p>
         </div>
