               <item n="m_philcomment_old">&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.1d &lt;i&gt;ye pramattāḥ sadā mṛtāḥ&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.21 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a1.&lt;/b&gt; &lt;i&gt;smṛtā(ḥ)&lt;/i&gt; seems to be an error for &lt;i&gt;mṛtāḥ&lt;/i&gt;, possibly induced by &lt;i&gt;sadā&lt;/i&gt; (also in the Tib. version, see [[Lévi 1912a]]: 235), which corresponds to &lt;i&gt;yathā&lt;/i&gt; in e.g. the Dhp. Thus, Dhp.21d &lt;i&gt;ye pamattā yathā matā&lt;/i&gt; 'the careless are as though [already] dead' ([[Norman 2004]]: 4) corresponds to &lt;i&gt;ye pramattāḥ sadā smṛtāḥ&lt;/i&gt; 'who are negligent are always remembered' in this version (this reading is not given by [[Bernhard 1965]]: 126).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.2a-b &lt;i&gt;etāṃ viśeṣatāṃ jñātvā hy apramādasya paṇḍitaḥ&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.22 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a2.&lt;/b&gt; The hiatus-resolving &lt;i&gt;hy&lt;/i&gt; is lacking before &lt;i&gt;apramā(dasya)&lt;/i&gt; (this occurs frequently with these pādas divided in two, because there is no hiatus anyway, cf. [[Thomas 1974]]: 82, [[Thomas 1977a]]: 271 and e.g. [[THT 101]] a3 &lt;i&gt;as(m)iṃ&lt;/i&gt; for &lt;i&gt;hy asmiṃ&lt;/i&gt;).&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.2c &lt;i&gt;apramādaṃ pramudyeta&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.22 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;a4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.3a &lt;i&gt;apramattāḥ sātatikā&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.23(and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b3.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.4e &lt;i&gt;parvatasthaiva bhūmisthāṃ&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.28 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b4.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.4f &lt;i&gt;dhīro bālān avekṣate&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.28 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b5.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.5b &lt;i&gt;saṃyamena damena ca&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.25 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;
&lt;p&gt;&lt;b&gt;b6.&lt;/b&gt; Uv.4.5c-d &lt;i&gt;dvīpaṃ karoti medhāvī tam ogho nābhimardati&lt;/i&gt;, see Dhp.25 (and [[Norman 2004]]: 4)&lt;/p&gt;</item>
